3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a hierarchical planning and coordination structure to ensure the coordination performance of large-scale robot networks, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a greedy task allocation method to assign tasks to robots, which can be considered as an AI problem. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly mention the use of machine learning, it is possible that machine learning techniques are used for some aspects of the proposed approach, such as generating the dynamic traffic heat-map.
